Senior Programs Coordinator
United Nations Pakistan
-
Islamabad
Under the overall and direct supervision of the Chief of Mission in Islamabad, and in cooperation with relevant units in IOM Islamabad, the successful candidate will be responsible for the following responsibilities. The incumbent will:
Coordinate and support supervision and management of effective and efficient IOM programmes related to migration management in collaboration with relevant counterparts in the government and development partners in the country
Analyse and interpret trends, challenges and priorities in Pakistan with regard to migration management interventions and maintain partnerships with national authorities and institutions working on the same issues
Represent IOM in relevant internal/external meetings, working groups and coordination forums and respond to requests for information on projects.
Contribute to development of and implement awareness raising activities in coordination with implementing counterparts as required
Ensure project implementation and monitor progress of the project by evaluating the projects together with government counterparts and other partners keeping the COM informed on the status of implementation of each project
Coordinate daily administration of the programme department
Coordinate with Government counterparts in relation to IOMâs country programme implementation/management in the areas of migration management and ensure results-based programme delivery
Ensure project implementation and evaluate lessons learnt for further integration into project outlines keeping in view newly developed policies and good practices and establishing appropriate execution and monitoring mechanisms and systems
Stay up to date regarding assessments and reports produced by other agencies and organizations and ensure relevant and important information is incorporated in IOM reports, project proposals and strategies.
Prepare programme/project status reports required for management, donors, budget review, programme analysis, annual reports, etc.
Liaise with other local government, International Organizations, national and international institutions and NGOs, and other members of civil society working on common issues
Support IOM resource mobilization efforts by preparing relevant documentation and participating in donor meetings and public information events
Support and strengthen IOMâs strategic alliances and partnerships for effective and comprehensive activities in the area of migration management
Organize coordination meetings, workshops, working groups and donor meetings relating to migration management, within the country and regionally with various counterparts as per requirement
Perform any other duties assigned by the Chief of Mission
Education and Experience:
Completed university degree from an accredited academic institution preferably in Social Sciences or related discipline; b) 3 years of experience in projects implementation; c) previous work experience in Central or South Asia, particularly in Pakistan, on similar programming highly advantageous especially as regards to proof of EU Readmission project knowledge/expertise and implementation.
Languages:
Thorough knowledge of English & Urdu
